&lt;p&gt;AdvancedMD is a unified cloud suite of medical office software hosted on Amazon Web Services/AWS including practice management, electronic health records, and patient engagement, and offers managed medical billing services for independent practices.&amp;nbsp;AdvancedMD serves an expansive national footprint of 65,000 practitioners across 14,000 practices and 900 independent medical billing companies. 8.8M insurance claims are processed every month on the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.advancedmd.com/company/media-coverage/&quot;&gt;AdvancedMD billing&lt;/a&gt; platform!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a detail-oriented systems professional with a passion for operational excellence and healthcare technology? AdvancedMD is looking for a driven and experienced &lt;strong&gt;Revenue Operations NetSuite Analyst&lt;/strong&gt; to join our growing team. In this role, you will be responsible for administering, optimizing, and scaling NetSuite to support the end-to-end revenue lifecycle across Sales, Marketing, and Customer Success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Revenue Operations NetSuite Analyst&lt;/strong&gt;, you’ll leverage your expertise in CRM/ERP systems and data operations to translate complex business needs into scalable system solutions—owning NetSuite configurations, reporting, and integrations that directly power revenue growth. You’ll partner closely with go-to-market teams and cross-functional stakeholders to ensure data accuracy, streamlined lead processes, and actionable reporting that drives informed decision-making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone who thrives in a fast-paced, collaborative environment and is passionate about building the operational infrastructure that enables healthcare technology companies to scale. If you’re ready to take ownership of critical systems and make a measurable impact on revenue performance, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Job Duties:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NetSuite Administration: Manage day-to-day administration of NetSuite from a Sales/Revenue Operations perspective, including configuration and maintenance of fields, workflows, dashboards, roles, and permissions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;System Support &amp;amp; Troubleshooting: Diagnose and resolve system issues, support CPQ functionality, and drive enhancements that improve platform reliability and user experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting &amp;amp; Forecasting: Build and maintain reports and dashboards that provide pipeline visibility, support accurate forecasting, and deliver actionable insights to leadership and go-to-market teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Routing &amp;amp; Lifecycle Management: Design and manage lead routing logic and lifecycle processes to ensure seamless handoffs between Marketing, Sales, and Customer Success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Integrity: Ensure data accuracy across systems, proactively resolve inconsistencies, and enforce best practices to maintain a single source of truth across the revenue stack&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process Automation: Identify and implement opportunities to automate manual processes, reducing administrative burden and improving operational efficiency across teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration: Partner closely with Sales, Marketing, Finance, and Product to understand business needs and translate them into scalable system solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documentation &amp;amp; Enablement: Create and maintain documentation, training resources, and user guides to empower NetSuite users across the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
